Introduction

Base URL: http://localhost

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

POST api/register

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"pqtxqrgrxkvlzqsasnosovz\",
    \"phone\": \"029912\",
    \"email\": \"nkeeling@example.net\",
    \"city_id\": \"rerum\",
    \"password\": \"836%sXD5\\/-M<]-p3\\/\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "pqtxqrgrxkvlzqsasnosovz",
    "phone": "029912",
    "email": "nkeeling@example.net",
    "city_id": "rerum",
    "password": "836%sXD5\/-M<]-p3\/"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Le texte de value doit contenir au moins 5 caractères. Example: pqtxqrgrxkvlzqsasnosovz

phone   string   

Must match the regex /^[0-9+]+$/. Example: 029912

email   string   

Le champ value doit être une adresse e-mail valide. Example: nkeeling@example.net

city_id   string   

The id of an existing record in the cities table. Example: rerum

password   string   

Le texte de value doit contenir au moins 8 caractères. Example: 836%sXD5/-M<]-p3/

POST api/login

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"bertram.shields@example.org\",
    \"password\": \"Ou\\/e7xH`X*\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "bertram.shields@example.org",
    "password": "Ou\/e7xH`X*"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

Le champ value doit être une adresse e-mail valide. Le texte de value doit contenir au moins 5 caractères. Example: bertram.shields@example.org

password   string   

Le texte de value doit contenir au moins 4 caractères. Example: Ou/e7xHX*`

remember_checkbox   string  optional

GET api/product

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/api/product" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/api/product"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
